track_notes: From the free car park area at SD 289970. Walna Scar Road to Walna Scar (LDO-001 for WOTA). Continue on ridge to Dow Crag (LDW-047) and Brim Fell (LDW-037) Old Man is last. Return to CP skirting quarry to rejoin Walna Scar Road.
track_title: Old Man of Coniston with 3 Wainwrights

track_notes: This track from near The Sun Pub in Coniston village was walked in July 2010. It covers the Wainwights of Walna Scar, Dow Crag, Old Man,Brim Fell, Grey Friar, Great Carrs, Swirl How and Weatherlam.
track_title: Old man of Coniston with 7 Wainwights

track_notes: Also traverses Brim Fell, Dow Crag and Walna Scar for WOTA
track_title: An alternative ascent which also includes three Wainwrights

track_notes: This route is from Seathwaite in the Duddon Valley up the Walna Scar track then via Dow Cragg to the Old Man. There is a small parking area just beyond the gate at the start. It avoids the crowds at Coniston.

Total time (including ops): 2hr 55m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T5 / Grade 2 Scramble. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards.
